@startuml
autonumber
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ParticipantPadding 10

actor "User (Client/Admin)" as User
box "Frontend (Flutter Web/Mobile)" #LightBlue
  participant "ForgotPassword Screen" as Forgot
  participant "Router (AppRouter)" as Router
  participant "ResetPassword Screen" as Reset
end box

box "Backend (Supabase)" #LightGreen
  participant "Supabase Auth Service" as Auth
  database "PostgreSQL Database" as DB
end box

== Step 1: Password Reset Request ==
User -> Forgot : Enter professional email
Forgot -> Auth : resetPasswordForEmail(email, redirectTo = '/reset-password')
Auth -> User : Send email containing confirmation link

== Step 2: Link Click & Redirection ==
User -> Auth : Click recovery link in email client (e.g., Gmail)
note over Auth : Validate security token
Auth -> Router : Redirection to 'http://localhost:60604/reset-password#access_token=...'

== Step 3: Direct Routing & Session Initialization ==
note over Router : Analyze URL using usePathUrlStrategy() & onGenerateRoute()
Router -> Reset : Route directly to password change screen
note over Reset : Supabase client initializes session from URL access_token

== Step 4: Password Update ==
User -> Reset : Enter & confirm new password
Reset -> Auth : updatePassword(newPassword)
Auth -> DB : Update user password in auth.users
DB --> Auth : Success
Auth --> Reset : Confirmation of success
Reset -> User : Show "Success" dialog & redirect to Login screen

@enduml
